Slit skin of each plum lengthwise from top to bottom with a sharp paring knife evenly around plum in 4 to 6 places, then put in a heatproof jar. Bring water to a boil with remaining ingredients in a 3-quart nonreactive saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved, then simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes. Immediately pour pickling liquid over plums. Cool, uncovered, then chill, covered, at least 1 day. Available at Latino markets and Chile Todayâ€“Hot Tamale (800-468-7377). ** Available at Fauchon (212-308-5919).